a city work crew drenched by a passing 
motorist got even by tracking the man down and getting police to 
charge him with malicious splashing 
city worker tom boudreau and his partner who were monitoring 
the flow of water through storm sewers got drenched from head to 
foot when a car sped by and sent a 5foothigh gush of water over 
them 
mad as wet hens boudreau said they got in their pickup truck 
and tracked down robert petrin 24 at a drivein window of a bank 
i wasnt going to let him get away with that boudreau said 
friday 
petrin denied deliberately splashing the workers in the march 14 
incident but police charged him under a malicioussplashing law on 
the citys books since 1977 
a district court judge fined petrin 55 on april 5 when he 
failed to appear on the charge there was no telephone listing for 
petrin and he could not be located for comment friday 
public safety chief wayne heikkila said most motorists dont 
have to worry because were not going to stake out mud puddles 
