<TEXT>
wolf creek nuclear power plant officials 
found a nickel in the watercooled atomic reactor and are trying to 
determine if someone treated the vessel as a wishing well 
the coin was discovered wednesday during routine refueling and 
maintenace work about 25 feet down inside the reactor vessel 
were not sure how it got there in the first place whether it 
was accidental or done on purpose ronn smith a spokesman for 
wolf creek nuclear operating corp said friday 
workers tried to retrieve the nickel by lowering down a piece of 
lead with tape on it they momentarily snagged it but it broke 
loose and fell deeper smith said 
smith said analysts believe the coin will not pose a hazard or 
affect the operation of the reactor the nuclear regulatory 
commission has been informed he said 
the reactor vessel lies in a refueling pool of water used to 
help shield workers from radioactivity and protect the fuel rods 
its top section has been removed for the replacement of fuel rods 
the coin had fallen through the 23footdeep water and about 25 
feet inside the vessel a craneoperated bridge spans the pool and 
is placed directly over the reactor vessel when work is being done 
someone might have dropped the coin from the bridge or from 
elsewhere in the reactor containment building smith said 
</TEXT>
