<TEXT>
relax worried parents the national 
aeronautics and space administration its face red over a memo that 
fell off the vine says its safe for your kids to grow tomatoes 
from outer space 
even eat them if they must 
ive never heard of a killer tomato and i dont think weve 
got a killer tomato plant here either said alvin young director 
of the agriculture departments biotechnology office thats 
hollywood script stuff 
the space agency suffered a public relations crisis friday over 
a memo raising the possibility that tomatoes grown from 
spaceradiated seeds might be poisoned some 120000 packets of the 
seeds were distributed to 58000 teachers to be grown by their 
students 
the project is a safe and valuable educational outreach 
program said nasa it said it was assured by the agriculture 
department there were no food safety risks associated with the 
tomato seeds and fruits they produced 
but the memo from nelson j ehrlich obtained by the los angeles 
times said there is a remote possibility that a mutation could 
occur causing the plants to produce toxic fruit 
ehrlich is associate director for aerospace services at oklahoma 
state university which oversees nasas school programs and his 
memo was addressed to other supervisors of the project 
tomatoes ehrlich explained belong to the nightshade family of 
plants notorious for the production of toxic substances such as 
scopolamine atropine belladonna nicotine and solanine 
moreover he said foliage of the entire family is toxic 
nasa reacted by calling a news conference to say all is well it 
produced a new letter from ehrlich saying i have no evidence to 
support my statement other than the fact that the mechanism for 
toxin generation is present in tomatoes 
and said ehrlich he in no way intended to infer project 
participants would risk their lives by eating tomato fruits 
kenneth s pederson an associate administrator of the space 
agency told reporters i will be happy to eat the tomatoes my 
daughter is a schoolteacher her school is growing the tomatoes 
our whole family is going to eat the tomatoes 
young said raising the tomatoes is safe but that hed prefer 
that schoolchildren replant the seeds to carry out the experiment 
rather than eat them 
the possibility of a child having an allergic reaction to 
tomatoes grown from the seeds is very remote he said 
i realize we are going to put 12 million seeds out there 
potentially but i really doubt that the number is going to be big 
enough for us to produce a toxic mutation young said he added 
theres no 100 percent assurance however 
there is no more danger from eating these tomatoes than from 
eating those you find in a grocery store said jim alston 
research director for park seed co of greenwood sc which 
supplied the seeds in 1984 there is no radiation inherent in the 
seeds 
alston said radiation counters showed absolutely nothing 
when the seeds were returned to earth in january 
i am a parent i have kids he said if my kid was 
participating i would have no hesitation for them handling 
them 
the seeds were in one of 57 experiment trays fastened to the 
outside of a 12sided frame that had been in orbit since 1984 when 
it was retrieved in january by space shuttle columbia 
the satellite named the long duration exposure facility was 
testing a number of different materials to determine how they 
withstood the rigors of space 
</TEXT>
