<TEXT>
in the israeli town of kfar chabad a 
tudorstyled anomoly rises amid the holy lands jumble of ancient 
and modern edifices 
it is a replica of another building 6000 miles away at 770 
eastern parkway in brooklyn the headquarters of menachem mendel 
schneerson the 88yearold leader of the lubavitcher hasidim 
it is also a symbol of the fealty of schneersons followers 
that loyalty some political observers say this week scuttled an 
attempt by the labor party to form an israeli government 
two members of the knesset refused to back labor citing 
schneersons opposition to trading land for peace a cornerstone of 
the labor platform 
schneerson has again obstructed the formation of a government 
in israel allan nadler who teaches jewish studies at mcgill 
university in montreal complained in a column in the new york 
times today 
once again the parliament finds itself in the stranglehold of 
an orthodox rabbi for whom the welfare of the state of israel is 
entirely subordinate to parochial theological considerations 
nadler wrote 
rabbi yehuda krinsky a spokesman for schneerson denied that 
schneerson had issued any dictum to the rebellious legislators the 
rebbe or grand rabbi had not talked to either he said and had 
taken no sides in israels political crisis 
schneerson did comment obliquely on the landforpeace issue 
in a speech several weeks ago and one of the two legislators 
rabbi avraham verdiger called the rebbes office to ask if 
schneerson had changed his position 
told he had not verdiger repudiated labor on his own 
initiative krinsky said lubavitch has not been involved in 
any of the political horsetrading thats going on 
schneersons name has come up in previous israeli controversies 
opponents claimed that he was behind efforts to amend the law so 
the converts of nonorthodox rabbis would not gain automatic 
citizenship in israel 
in the united states his followers have earned the enmity of 
other jewish groups by supporting moments of silent prayer in 
public schools and by pressing for the right to erect hanukkah 
menorahs in public places 
the man at the center of these disputes is a small figure 
distinguished by his black fedora white beard and penetrating blue 
eyes 
born in russia an immigrant in 1941 he has never been to 
israel in fact apart from twiceyearly visits to his 
fatherinlaws grave in queens he has not left brooklyn at all 
since he took office in 1950 
schneerson is the seventh in the line of lubavitcher rebbes 
going back to his greatgreatgreatgreatgrandfather rabbi 
schneur zalman an acolyte of the founder of hasidism the baal 
shem tov 
the lubavitchers like other hasidim are pious folk the men 
wear black and are bearded the women cut their hair and wear wigs 
after marriage 
but unlike the others the lubavitchers are outwardlooking 
eager to persuade other jews to become more observant 
schneerson has presided over a rapid expansion of the 
lubavitcher universe more than 1000 chabad houses have been 
established around the world to spread the word the rebbes 
speeches sometimes extending six hours are sent by satellite to 
cable systems around the world recreational vans known as 
jewish tanks roam the country to promote jewish ritual 
lubavitcher officials claim a million followers around the 
world others dispute that figure but agree that the movement is 
influential 
lubavitch is the single most powerful movement in the jewish 
world said rabbi irving greenburg an orthodox rabbi and critic 
of the lubavitchers who heads the center for learning and 
leadership 
schneerson is the movements soul more than 125 volumes of his 
talks writings and correspondence have been published his 
pictures hang everywhere in israel his advice is sought on all 
matters whether a couple should marry the solution to a business 
question even says krinsky the answer to complex mathematical 
problems 
his followers recall seemingly miraculous consequences of 
schneersons suggestions lives that were saved babies that were 
born marriages that were made 
these stories have led some to ask whether the rebbe is actually 
the messiah come to earth to redeem the jews 
such talk outrages other jewish leaders schneerson has never 
claimed to be the messiah krinsky says only that if the messiah 
should come the rebbe said to be a descendent of king davids 
would be qualified 
krinsky says there can be no dispute about one thing theres 
no greater spiritual leader in the world jewish community 
</TEXT>
