fire investigators have been able to 
pinpoint where a hotel fire that killed nine elderly people 
started but not how 
they have ruled out arson however in the april 6 fire at the 
residential fontana hotel 
we have sifted and gone through practically every foot of dirt 
and debris that was in the building it was not a set fire 
malcolm brady chief of the miami office of the us bureau of 
alcohol tobacco and firearms said friday 
nearly 100 residents were left homeless by the deadliest fire 
ever in the oceanside city 
investigators are certain the fire started in a crawl space 
below the third floor of the 102room hotel where residents had 
reported a water leak and plumbers had been working less than 24 
hours earlier brady said 
however after more than 250 interviews expert analysis of burn 
patterns and a search by an accelerantsniffing dog state and 
federal fire investigators failed to pinpoint the cause of the 
blaze 
its tremendously frustrating for all of us to arrive on a 
scene thats taken nine lives and not to be able to come to you 
conclusively and say this is what caused it brady said 
the blaze was so intense that temperatures reached more than 
1200 degrees steel melted and and crucial evidence was destroyed 
brady said 
it probably smoldered in that crawl space for a number of 
hours literally consuming itself until it ignited brady said 
some of the evidence we needed is gone forever 
authorities have identified all nine bodies recovered from the 
threestory hotel located between the citys trendy art deco 
district and a strip of luxury highrise condominiums 
investigators dont expect the death toll to rise five other 
occupants reported as missing after the fire have since been 
located 
all nine victims ranging in age from 75 to 93 died of smoke 
inhalation said dr katherine berg of dade county medical 
examiners office 
more than 60 searchers including arson experts from the atf and 
city and state fire marshals offices took part in the 
investigation and workers continued to comb through the blackened 
shell of the building friday 
