<TEXT>
a woman cancer patient who rejected 
chemical and radiation treatment so she could give birth to a 
healthy baby has died 
linda babcock 41 gave birth to a 5pound 6ounce boy feb 23 
while battling an inoperable lung cancer known as oat cell 
carcinoma she had rejected treatment for fear of damaging the baby 
and refused to have an abortion 
the baby jesse is doing fine 
hes a beautiful son ill find a way to take care of him 
mrs babcocks husband george said friday night 
the baby kept her going he said 
shortly after she gave birth mrs babcock said in an interview 
from her room at st joseph medical center in bloomington that she 
didnt believe she had cancer anymore 
i feel so much better i can breathe i could tell it was 
there before it felt like something cutting off my air taking my 
life she had said 
im confident of living of beating the cancer the baby 
saved me from death as i saved him 
