not just any eggs easter eggs more specifically the colorful 
plastic grass that goes underneath them 
mount union in central pennsylvania is home to one of the 
nations leading producers of easter basket grass the plant where 
the crinkly grass is made helped revitalize the towns economy when 
it opened in 1979 a time when brickyard kilns were cooling from a 
downturn in building 
the 105 employees of the bleyer industries inc factory have a 
busy season from november to a couple of weeks before easter but 
the plant runs all year round branching into tinted plastic wrap 
at other times of the year with a reduced staff 
we made 18 million bags of grass this season said manager 
frank lukens weve been making about a million more bags each 
year 
liquid polypropylene arrives at the plant by rail and is 
converted to sheets of tinted plastic then stretched and run 
through 10 machines with slits spaced oneeighth inch apart lukens 
said the grass kinks when the tension is relaxed then handfuls 
are stuffed into 1 2 3 or 4ounce bags adorned with bunnies 
or the grass is rolled into 80pound bales 
the grass comes in pink yellow and green 
during the easter rush the plant runs 10 hours a day six days 
a week some large chocolate and gift makers such as russell 
stover candies in kansas city mo make their own grass to 
accompany their easter products 
more than 6000 people lived in mount union in the middle of the 
century turning clay from nearby mountains into bricks but the 
population steadily fell to the present level of 3000 as three 
large brick factories closed over the last 20 years the last in 
january 
the town went scrambling for replacement businesses and borough 
manager frank stasenko said it has succeeded in diversifying its 
economy in addition to the easter grass factory mount union is 
home to a plant that makes fiberglass tanks for gasoline stations 
and another that makes pipe fittings 
weve been as low as were going to get stasenko said 
