<TEXT>
the growing number of law firms that offer 
investment advice public relations help and other services has 
prompted the nations largest lawyer group to consider restrictions 
the issue has become even more urgent since the previously 
unthinkable is about to happen nonlawyers will wield much the 
same clout within some law firms as lawyers 
its a pretty explosive issue said dick collins an 
american bar association spokesman to the oldtime definition of 
professionalism this is anathema nevertheless this sort of thing 
is out there and we will have to deal with it 
the abas policymaking house of delegates will be presented at 
its convention in august with recommendations to limit lawyers 
providing nonlegal services and to ban nonlawyers from becoming 
law firm partners 
if adopted as official aba policy the recommendations will 
serve as models for legal ethics rules enforced by each state 
law firms and the rules that govern them may be headed in the 
opposite direction however 
in the district of columbia where law firm diversification got 
its first foothold local rules underwent a revolutionary 
firstinthenation revision last month to allow nonlawyers to 
become partners 
the changes which take effect in january are an attempt to 
help law firms attract and retain skills not traditionally found 
among lawyers said robert e jordan iii a prime backer of the 
new rules 
jordans prestigious law firm of steptoe amp johnson along with 
several others in the nations capital have for years provided 
