governing zimbabwe african national union patriotic front ends 
up benefiting chiefly the people already entrenched in powerful 
positions the church commission said 
no generation has the right to make immutable decisions for 
future generations it said 
in one of its strongest attacks on mugabes policies the 
commission said the freedom to vote for a political party of choice 
was a fundamental right along with the freedoms of association 
assembly and speech enshrined in constitutional law 
it urged the governing party to rule with a mandate based on 
freedom of choice and its own efficiency and credibility of 
performance 
after the governing party won 116 of 119 seats contested by five 
parties in parliamentary elections last month mugabe said the 
victory at the polls gave him the backing he needed to establish a 
oneparty system along marxist lines 
he has repeatedly argued that a plural system creates division 
that hinders development 
since zimbabwes independence in 1980 the governing party has 
abided by the britishmediated constitution containing safeguards 
for political opposition 
those safeguards expire when zimbabwe celebrates its 10th 
anniversary of independence from white minority rule on wednesday 
but mugabe has said he will not immediately outlaw opposition 
parties 
