some of the writing that emanated from last 
springs pro democracy demonstrations in beijings tiananmen 
square has been saved for historians in the new york public library 
about 700 items declarations poetry newsletters and the like 
were gathered in china by robin munro a researcher for the human 
rights group asia watch the material has been donated to archives 
about the prodemocracy movement around the world including one at 
the library in manhattan 
