in her recreation room when the quake hit and wondered briefly 
whether it would ruin the new addition to her home 
it actually looked like the walls were moving in different 
directions she said 
i couldnt believe it said wally beketa of nearby custer 
the bed shook the mirrors danced on the walls 
there were no reports of damage in british columbia 
the richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake measuring 4 is capable of causing moderate damage 
5 considerable damage and 6 can be severe 
</TEXT>
