american commission an independent body appointed by successive 
presidents is less sure 
since the united states is outside the ec european 
community measures that reduce internal barriers but leave 
external barriers unchanged cause trade diversion that is 
increased trade among ec member states at the expense of trade 
between the united states and the ec it said 
its study is called the effects of greater economic 
integration within the european community on the united states 
first followup report dated for march it was distributed to 
reporters this week 
on the television issue american pressure helped soften a 
european proposal to require that 60 percent of all broadcasts in 
the 12 countries originate in one of them a european directive 
adopted last october asked some preferential treatment for programs 
originating in europe but it set no binding limits leaving each 
of the member governments to set them if they choose 
the us government and the us industry have continued to 
object to the local content provisions of the directive both on the 
grounds that they are protectionist and that they interfere with 
freedom of expression the us commission said 
it also saw possible benefits to us business from greater 
unity in western europe american industry that competes with 
european exports will benefit as european products go more to 
european countries rather than overseas it said and added that 
any measures to reduce european barriers against imports will lower 
the price of american goods to european buyers 
