for instance degange said previous research in the sound has 
shown that most winterkill otters are either very young or very 
old 
the young are still learning how to survive and the old are 
in poor condition he said 
scientists can tell the age of the dead by inspecting their 
teeth so if more than a few middleaged otter carcasses are 
collected this spring it will indicate some unnatural cause such 
as eating oiled clams or mussels may be killing otters 
studies last summer found that spilled crude had poisoned 
otters which suffered liver and lung damage the wildlife agency 
is ordering autopsies for some of this springs carcasses it also 
is analyzing tissue samples from others to check for oil poisoning 
