poisoning in the garage of trepals home in alturas 
a homemade journal on poisoning in trepals home in sebring 
where he moved after mrs carrs death including literature about 
thallium nitrate and medical examination procedures 
laboratory equipment at the sebring home chemicals and a small 
amount of what authorities believe is the illegal drug crank 
a secret soundproof room and equipment for apparent use in 
torture and bondage in the basement of the sebring home 
investigator ernest mincey said he has detailed several 
confrontations between trepal and the carr family mincey said 
investigators believe trepal may have used the same poison to kill 
the carr family dogs several years ago 
peggy carr 41 became sick in october 1988 after drinking from 
16ounce soda bottles at her home she eventually was placed on 
lifesupport equipment and died march 3 1989 
her son duane dubberly 17 and stepson travis carr 18 were 
left paralyzed tests of mrs carrs husband parearlyn carr and 
three other people showed traces of the chemical but they were not 
hospitalized 
fbi analysis showed the bottles had been laced with thallium 
nitrate a colorless tasteless chemical that is highly toxic 
prosecutors said trepal is a chemist who had been sentenced to 
federal prison in the mid1970s for helping run a methamphetamine 
manufacturing operation in north carolina 
part of the production of methamphetamine mincey said requires 
an elaborate chemical process in which thallium nitrate is used 
mincey said investigators also determined no member of the carr 
family purchased the soft drink suggesting that someone familiar 
with the familys comings and goings entered the house and left the 
bottles when no one was home 
we have evidence that mr trepal often watched the carr 
residence through binoculars mincey said 
friends have said trepal and his wife orthopedic specialist 
diana carr no relation to the neighboring carr family would 
stage annual mystery murder weekends in which the fictional 
murders were poisoninduced 
